To set up a macro, just type 'macro <macroname> <macro>'.  Use a semi-colon
or a colon for multiple commands.  Use a %n to insert the nth argument in
the macro.  Use $n to insert the nth argument in the macro, plus all the
arguments afterwards.

Use 'unmacro <macroname>' to remove a macro.

Some examples of macros:
  macro ar edit area;reset;exit
    - resets the entire area, then exits the OLC
  macro cr edit room;mod;door;%1;dest;%2;exit
    - connects the room direction %1 to vnum %2
      ex:  'cr north 3011' will connect the north exit to vnum 3011
  macro rname edit room;mod;name;$1;exit
    - renames a room
      ex:  'rname The Temple of Mojo'
~
