CLAN MUTINY POLICIES:

AVARICE:

To mutiny the leader of Avarice, it is very simple. All you
need to do, is:
1.  Announce intent with the support of 1 /4.  (If you are
a /4, thats fine, support of any other member is acceptable.
2.  A vote will be held, winner takes all.  If there is a tie
then it is settled by dual.
3.  Anyone guilded within 2 weeks of the Mutiny is NOT permitted
a vote.
4.  The loser will be required to leave all EQ behind.  This is
so the leader (Whom may be holding clan funds) doesn't make
it out the door and screw the clan.  It will be up to the
winner to return any other gear.  (which would follow charter)

DEMISE:

To mutiny in Demise, you need to have five supporters who
are different characters, and you must organize the mutiny
in seret, posting the mutiny note to Demise and the immortals
once the supporters, one of which must be a /4, have been
arranged.  Otherwise, the current leader is entitled to 
outcast you at any time prior to the public posting.
In addition, you yourself must have been in Demise for
a period of two months, not necessairly consecutive months
provided you didn't join any other clan if you were a loner
at some point.  Once these requirements have been satisified,
a duel will take place in which each side may declare a champion
to fight in their place.  The winning side becomes the leader.

HONOR:

Any Mutineer must have attained the rank of /2 or above and have at
least 5 supporters, those of rank /3 only require 4 supporers, and
those of rank /4 only require 3 supporters. He must then post a note 
declaring the mutiny that includes character info, mutiny reasons and 
the names of his supporters.  If this is done, and the supporters are 
verified,1 week of voting will commence. An immortal will count the 
votes. No recruiting will take place during the week of voting.  Voting 
with alts will disqualify a person's votes.  The mutineer and /5's may 
not vote.The loser of the mutiny will be ranked /1 and will hand over all
valuables to the victor.

POSSE:

If you wish to challenge for leadership, it works as a simple
majority vote. In order to be elligible you must first gain 
support from at least 3 other posse members.Once you have 
necessary support, the election begins. Majority wins.
The parties involved (being the Leader challenged and the 
challenger) can not vote.

WARLOCK:

Majority Vote was method used in past, so as it stands that 
is the policy. An Imm would be asked to tally votes.
Mutineer would post cnote to 'Warlock Immortal' declaring mutiny
and giving name of IMM to post your vote to.
(so votes can be anonymous) 7 days from post date, vote is tallied, 
winner is /5 looser is outcast.

ZEALOT:

To mutiny in Zealot, the mutineer must be a rank /4, and have the
support of at least 5 other members who have been ranked above /0
and who have been in the clan for at least one month's time.
The Anointed then has the choice to either settle the dispute
via a duel, or a clan vote.
If a duel is called for, an IMM will supervise on a preset date which
will be at least one week after the mutiny was called. The duel will
be to the death, with no charmies. Cheaters will lose automatically.
If the Anointed does not wish to duel, he or she may call for a
clan vote, which shall last for a period of one week. During that
time, all /4s shall be reduced to /0 until the vote is decided, or
one of the contesting parties withdraws.

The loser of either contest will be at the winner's discretion.

~
