The Infamous Prefresh

Q. What is it?
A. The prefresh is short for "player refresh".  It is a process by which all
current player files (the file that contains the data about your character in
fixed storage) and updated to the current MHS game code.

Q. How often will we do this?
A. If we do it right and make changes correectly, once and once only.

Q. How will I know when I am being prefreshed?
A. You will be given a 10-day advanced warning before we do it.  We will also
run a handful of tests that players can volunteer to put themselves through
to make sure there are no bugs.

Q. What will happen to my character when I prefresh?
A. When the day arrives you will log in and the game will detect that your
character is not marked as being prefreshed already.  You'll be put into a
sort of secondary creation mode.  You will be told that you need to prefresh
and an image of your player file will be backed up to a special directory just
in case something goes wrong.  The game will store in a special data structure
a copy of your important data, and then you'll have to select which method of
prefresh you want to use.  You'll be guided through the process from there.

Q. What are my options?
A. Option #1 is the Standard Prefresh.  What happens is that your character
is set to level 1 and you go to the alignment selection screen.  You pick your
alignment, and then you to the stat customization screen.  Once that is done,
you are put back into the game at level 1, and your skills will all default
back to their original values.  When you type "score", you'll see that you
have an item called "debit levels".  You may use these at any time to level.


