As an Immortal on MHS, there are certain things expected of you, and
especially as a newer immortal, you should be mindful of exactly what
it is you're supposed to be doing.  Below is a short summary of what's
expected of an Immortal at each of the 7 levels.

Note:  Not fulfilling the expectations of your job can result in demotion.

All levels:  Ensure that the rules are being followed.  If someone is
cheating, either snap them back in line yourself, or ask for the aid of
a higher level Immortal.  You must be completely neutral in all dealings
with mortals, meaning you must treat your friends exactly the same as
you would your enemies.  Personal feelings have no place in the job of
an Immortal.

52 - Retired.  This is the level where immortals who have become inactive
or have voluntarily retired are placed.  There are no real expectations,
save to follow the same rules as everyone else.

53 - Trial IMM.  This is the first level you will be placed at as an
Immortal.  At this level, your future IMMhood is dependant upon how
you act during this time.  Sometimes, Immortals don't work out, and if
you are found to be one of the ones who isn't working out, you'll be
placed at 52.  Expectations at this level are minor:  help enforce the
rules, run a few minor quests, but most importantly, learn the lay of the
land, the limited commands available to you at this time, the rules of
being an Immortal, and begin statting mobs to get an idea of how mob
strength is balanced against level.  At this level, you should be asking
questions often, and seeking input to the majority of your decisions.

55 - Newbie IMM.  At this level, you have a few more commands available
to you, most notably string.  You've pass the majority of the 'trial'
stage, but you're still expected to be learning.  This is the first level
where you will have access to On-Line Construction (OLC), and you'll be
given a small set of vnums to practice your building skills.  Expectations
at this level:  help enforce the rules, handle restrings for players, learn
OLC, continue learning the balances of mob and item strength vs. level.
You have a bit more free reign when it comes to making decisions, but any
major decision should still be brought forward to a more experienced
Immortal.

