Immortalhood, and you have the majority of the commands in the game used
to penalize other players and handle day-to-day situations.  By now, you
should have a firm grasp of the rules of MHS and the rules of IMMhood,
and a working relationship with the rest of the IMMteam.  Expectations at
this level are:  be active, enforce the rules, run quests, handle strings,
build on OLC, and deal with any other day-to-day situations that may arise.
Your conduct may still be up for review if you're found to be lacking, but
you're no longer at risk for being cut from the team for not 'fitting in'
once you've reached this point.

58 - Senior Immortal.  Immortals who've proven that they have a solid grasp
of the way MHS and the IMMteam works, and the maturity to handle almost any
situation with a cool, neutral demeanor may find themselves promoted to
Senior Immortal.  The job expectations don't change, but you are given some
of the more sensitive commands on MHS with which to work.  Not all
Immortals will make it this far, and the ones that do should be respected
for their dedication to MHS.

59 - Admin.  Admins supervise the lower level Immortals, while still 

keeping up all of the expectations of all the other jobs.  They have
their hands full of responsibility, and almost every command available
on MHS, including reboot and permban.  If, as a lower level Immortal,
you have a question as to a rule, either for mortals or for Immortals,
or you need feedback on an idea that you've had but you aren't sure
about, speak to an Admin.  They've been around long enough to know MHS
inside and out, and can answer any question you have for them.  Some Admins
are also Coders, and have the additional responsibility of writing new
code for the game, and eradicating bugs from existing code.

60 - Implementor.  If you need to be told what your job as an Implementor
is, you should probably put down the crack pipe now...

